folder: Barry Street & Rossville Avenue, Staten Island, NY
text:

Barry Street, west of the N. W. corner of Rossville Avenue, showing Washington Hall. Robinson's Atlases of 1898 and 1907 show it to be the school of St. Joseph's Roman Catholic Church.

The same, at a later date.

folder: Knesel Street & Rossville Avenue, Staten Island, NY
text:
Knesel Street (center, from left to right), adjoining the N.E. corner of Rossville Avenue, showing the site to be an empty lot. The view is northward across Knesel Street from an empty lot on the south side. The house shown fronts on Morris Street.

April 30, 1929.

P. L. Speer

folder: Knesel Street & Rossville Avenue, Staten Island, NY
text:

Knesel Street, east from Rossville Avenue.

P. L. Sperr,

April 30, 1929

(2)
A closer view of two of the houses on the north side of the street(seen in view 1). Beers' 1874 map shows the first house to have belonged to C. Kreisel, and the second, bearing No. 29-31, to W. Gaton.

P. L. Sperr,

April 30, 1929.

(3)
The same as view 1, at a later date.

P. L. Sperr,

May 5, 1937.
